    AI Overview
    Test automation is the use of specialized software to run tests on a software application and compare the results against expected outcomes without manual intervention. This process uses scripts to automate repetitive testing tasks, which saves time, increases efficiency, improves accuracy, and allows for faster and more frequent testing compared to manual methods. It is a crucial practice in modern software development, supporting methodologies like CI/CD (Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery) by providing quick feedback on the quality of code changes.
     
    This video explains what test automation is and when it is appropriate:
    45s
    Software Testing by Daniel Knott
    YouTube Aug 12, 2024
    Key aspects of test automation
    • What it is:
      It's a method for executing tests using pre-written scripts to validate software functionality, performance, and reliability. 
    • How it works:
      Automation tools control the execution of tests, enter data, and verify that the actual results match the predicted results, which is then reported automatically. 
    • Benefits:
      • Efficiency and speed: Automating tests runs them much faster than manual testing, allowing for more frequent and thorough checks. 
      • Accuracy: Automation reduces human error, leading to more consistent and reliable test results. 
      • Cost savings: Over time, the efficiency gains can lead to lower costs associated with testing. 
      • Better coverage: It enables more extensive test coverage, as repetitive tests can be run automatically without manual fatigue. 
    • Types of testing that can be automated:
      • Unit testing: Verifying that individual pieces of code work correctly. 
      • Integration testing: Ensuring different modules of code work together as expected. 
      • End-to-end testing: Validating that the entire application flow meets user expectations. 
      • Regression testing: Checking that new changes haven't broken existing functionality. 
    • Role in development:
      It integrates into the software development lifecycle to support continuous delivery and integration (CI/CD) by providing rapid validation of every new code commit. 
    • Relationship with manual testing:
      Test automation does not aim to eliminate manual testing. Instead, it reduces the number of repetitive tasks that need to be done manually, allowing human testers to focus on more complex and exploratory testing.

      What do you mean by test automation?
      Test automation is the use of software (separate from the software being tested) for controlling the execution of tests and comparing actual outcome with predicted. Test automation supports testing the system under test (SUT) without manual interaction which can lead to faster test execution and testing more often.

      What is the difference between QA and test automation?
      QA vs Automation

      QA is a broader discipline encompassing processes, standards, and activities to ensure overall product quality. Automation refers explicitly to using technology to perform tasks without human intervention and, in testing, focuses on automated test execution.
